them are considered primary. Yoginis are attendants of the d=\r\nivine Mother. These are the experiences surrounding self-consciousness. Yog=\r\ninis represent Shakti and Bhairavas represent Purusha.\n \nAt the low level, =\r\nBhairavas are personifications of various subtle experiences. At the highes=\r\nt level, Yoginis and Bhairavas are personifications of observing various su=\r\nbtle experiences. Yoginis personify the observation and Bhairavas the obser=\r\nver.\n \nA fully realized person is neither attracted to nor repelled by any =\r\nexperience. As various experiences come, one simply observes. Bhairava is a=\r\nn observer of various experiences within.\n \nBest regards,\nNarasimha\n-------=\r\n-----------------------------------------------------------\nDo a Short Homa=\r\nm Yourself: http://www.VedicAstrologer.org/homam\nDo Pitri Tarpanas Yourself=\r\n: http://www.VedicAstrologer.org/tarpana\nSpirituality: http://groups.yahoo.=\r\ncom/group/vedic-wisdom\nFree Jyotish lessons (MP3): http://vedicastro.home.c=\r\nomcast.net\nFree Jyotish software (Windows): http://www.VedicAstrologer.org\n=\r\nSri Jagannath Centre (SJC) website: http://www.SriJagannath.org\n-----------=\r\n------------------------------------------------------- \n\n  ----- Original =\r\nMessage ----- \n  From: rajarshi nandy \n  To: vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com \n=\r\n  Sent: Wednesday, February 18, 2009 11:29 PM\n  Subject: Re: [vedic-wisdom]=\r\n Re: MahaShivaratri - Shiva Homa Manual\n\n        Namaste Narasimhaji\n\n     =\r\n   Can you please give your thoughts on the difference between Rudra and Bh=\r\nairava.\n\n        -Regards\n         Rajarshi\n\n\n        The upsurge (of consc=\r\niousness) is Bhairava - Shiva Sutra\n\n\n        --- On Wed, 18/2/09, Narasimh=\r\na P.V.R. Rao &lt;pvr@...&gt; wrote:\n\n          From: Narasimha P.V.R. Rao=\r\n &lt;pvr@...&gt;\n          Subject: [vedic-wisdom] Re: MahaShivaratri - S=\r\nhiva Homa Manual\n          To: vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com\n